lead_paragraph: Rudy Gay had 32 points, nine rebounds and six assists as the Sacramento Kings snapped a five-game losing streak by defeating the Milwaukee Bucks 111-104 on Monday night.

headline.print_headline: Gay Scores 32 to Lead Kings Over Bucks, 111-104
